        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:41PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 341 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Rockingham, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockingham, Hoffman, Pinebluff, Ellerbe, Foxfire, Norman, Derby,
Sandhills Game Land, Camp Mackall, and Eagle Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
